      "body": "### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?\r\n\r\nforms\r\n\r\n### Is this a regression?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf a form is initialized multiply times with a new FormGroup, default disabled states of the controls will not apply.\r\n\r\nIt seems, that the form states (enabled/disabled) are somehow cached in the view. So, as a workaround, I destroyed the view and created a new one. You can see the workaround in the stackblitz, too.\r\n\r\n### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug\r\n\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-ivy-6fg5hd?file=src%2Fapp%2Fapp.component.ts\r\n\r\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\r\n\r\n```true\r\nThe view is not rendered correctly / form controls have wrong enabled/disabled states.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in (run `ng version`)\r\n\r\n```true\r\n\r\n     _                      _                 ____ _     ___\r\n    / \\   _ __   __ _ _   _| | __ _ _ __     / ___| |   |_ _|\r\n   / △ \\ | '_ \\ / _` | | | | |/ _` | '__|   | |   | |    | |\r\n  / ___ \\| | | | (_| | |_| | | (_| | |      | |___| |___ | |\r\n /_/   \\_\\_| |_|\\__, |\\__,_|_|\\__,_|_|       \\____|_____|___|\r\n                |___/\r\n\r\n\r\nAngular CLI: 13.1.1\r\nNode: 14.17.2\r\nPackage Manager: npm 6.14.13\r\nOS: darwin x64\r\n\r\nAngular: 13.1.0\r\n... animations, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core, forms\r\n... platform-browser, platform-browser-dynamic, router\r\n\r\nPackage                         Version\r\n---------------------------------------------------------\r\n@angular-devkit/architect       0.1301.1\r\n@angular-devkit/build-angular   13.1.1\r\n@angular-devkit/core            13.1.1\r\n@angular-devkit/schematics      13.1.1\r\n@angular/cli                    13.1.1\r\n@schematics/angular             13.1.1\r\nrxjs                            6.6.7\r\ntypescript                      4.5.4\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Anything else?\r\n\r\nThe stackblitz example is built with Angular 12, but the same bug appears on a local ng13 project.",
