      "body": "### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/releated to the feature request?\n\nanimations\n\n### Description\n\nTrigger callbacks for disabled and skipped animations are still being executed, this may not always be the desired behavior and may not be what developers always want.\r\n\r\nBut it does seem to be the intended code's behavior so it is not a bug (as the users can still get useful information in skipped animation callbacks).\r\n\r\nSo I was just thinking that maybe we could want to provide an option to avoid the execution of such callbacks\r\n\n\n### Proposed solution\n\nI think it could be nice to add a new field to the [BrowserAnimationsModuleConfig](https://angular.io/api/platform-browser/animations/BrowserAnimationsModuleConfig), something like `skipNoopAnimationCallbacks` or something like that, so that the user has the option to skip those callback if they prefer to \n\n### Alternatives considered\n\nThis proposed feature is only for convenience, I don't think that those callbacks are a big hindrance and that they can be manually ignored by checking the event's `totalTime` or `disabled` property in the function itself",
