      "body": "### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?\n\nDon't known / other\n\n### Is this a regression?\n\nNo\n\n### Description\n\nPlease see the reproduction. It seems zone.js assumes EventTarget's event call is always a standalone task, which may not be true.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst invoke = (fn) => {\r\n  document.body.addEventListener('click', fn);\r\n  document.body.click();\r\n  document.body.removeEventListener('click', fn);\r\n};\r\n\r\ninvoke(() => {\r\n  Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log(2));\r\n});\r\nconsole.log(1);\r\n```\n\n### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/typescript-88btqj?file=index.ts\n\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\n\n```true\nNative Chrome/Safari/Firefox outputs `1 2`, while with zone.js outputs `2 1`.\n```\n\n\n### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in (run `ng version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Anything else?\n\nI noticed this during debugging https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/41506#issuecomment-991765487 , maybe related.",
