      "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, I'm learning Angular. Reading through the documentation I noticed heavy use of terms like \"application\", \"module\", \"feature modules\", ... – whereas all these proprietary terms are not getting explained to the reader.\r\n\r\nThus, I'd like to suggest to add an introductory page to [Angular Routing](https://angular.io/guide/routing-overview), explaining …\r\na. these terms\r\nb. their task\r\nc. their general structure, and\r\nd. their relationship among each other.\r\n\r\n## Example\r\n\r\n### Description Of Angular Key Terms\r\n\r\n|Type|Task|Structure|Description|\r\n|-|-|-|-|\r\n|Application|…|…|…|\r\n|Module|…|…|…|\r\n|…|…|…|…|\r\n\r\n### Relationship\r\n![Hierarchy](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9283914/145627468-7c58bf70-b337-4548-a322-b0a335528212.png)\r\n\r\n## What is the affected URL?\r\n\r\nhttps://angular.io/guide/routing-overview",
